article.headline: Wright St. 66, Norfolk St. 43
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Cory Cooperwood had a season-high 19 points and eight rebounds as Wright State beat Norfolk State 66-43 Wednesday night. The Spartans (1-6) were within 10 with 10:06 to play, but Wright State (3-7) pulled away for good with a 21-6 run over the next 8 minutes. Norfolk State had its largest lead, 5-0, about 5 minutes into the game. But the Raiders scored nine unanswered points to pull ahead 15-9 with 7:28 left in the first half. They never trailed again. Wright State scored the 14 final points of the half to lead 29-12 at the break. Todd Brown came off the bench to add 10 points for Wright State. Corey Lyons led Norfolk State with 14 points, including four 3-pointers. Wright State shot 41.3 percent from the field and hit 23 of 29 free throws. The Spartans were 31.5 percent from the field and hit four of eight free throws.
